## Quick Start

{% if use_docker %}
### One-command start (Docker Compose)

The fastest way to run the full stack locally:

```bash
# Clone and enter the project
git clone <repo-url> {{ project_name }}
cd {{ project_name }}

# Copy environment files
cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env.local
cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local

# Start everything (api, web, {{ database }}{% if use_rabbitmq %}, rabbitmq{% endif %}{% if use_redis %}, redis{% endif %}, nginx)
docker compose up --build

# In a separate terminal, run database migrations
docker compose exec api php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate --no-interaction
```

The frontend is available at **http://localhost:3000** and the API at **http://localhost:8080**.

{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
API documentation (Swagger UI) is at **http://localhost:8080/api/docs**.
{% endif %}

---
{% endif %}

### Manual Setup (without Docker)

#### 1. Backend (Symfony)

```bash
cd apps/api

# Install PHP dependencies
composer install

# Configure the database
cp .env .env.local
# Edit apps/api/.env.local and set DATABASE_URL

# Create the database and run migrations
php bin/console doctrine:database:create
php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate --no-interaction

{% if use_auth and auth_method == "jwt" %}
# Generate JWT keypair
php bin/console lexik:jwt:generate-keypair
{% endif %}

# Start the development server
symfony server:start
# or: php -S 127.0.0.1:8000 -t public/
```

The API is now available at **http://localhost:8000**.

#### 2. Frontend (Next.js)

```bash
cd apps/web

# Install Node dependencies
pnpm install

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env.local
# Edit apps/web/.env.local and set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Start the development server
pnpm dev
```

The frontend is now available at **http://localhost:3000**.

